# Weather Checker App – Streamlit

## About the App
This project is a Python-based weather application developed using *Streamlit*.
The app allows users to enter a city name and retrieve **real-time weather information** using a REST API.

The project demonstrates the full development flow:
- Data retrieval via REST API
- Python logic separation
- Interactive web UI
- Version control with GitHub
- Deployment to Streamlit Cloud

---

## Live Application
The application is publicly deployed and accessible here:
https://pythonprojjf1-emodgcuywapkpwsyrj6nfu.streamlit.app/

---

## Features
- City-based weather search
- Displays:
  - Temperature
  - Humidity
  - Weather condition description
- Displays **current local date and time**:
  - User’s local time
  - Local time of the selected city (timezone-based)
- REST API integration (OpenWeatherMap)
- User-friendly and interactive UI built with Streamlit

---

## Technologies Used
- **Python**
- **Streamlit**
- **Requests** – REST API calls
- **Pandas** – data organization
- **OpenWeatherMap API**

